You’re on a weekly grocery run through a cursed retail labyrinth. Aisles shift. Samples whisper. Endcaps float. The store wants something from you.

Your goal: Get all the items on the list and make it to checkout alive.

### RULES OF TiGGR (Tiny Game for Generalized Roleplaying)

Stats: Body, Mind, Charm. Distribute 3 points (e.g. 2/1/0).  
Rolls: Roll 2d6 \+ relevant stat.  
Easy \= 6, Medium \= 8, Hard \= 10  
Attack: 2d6 \+ Body vs. 8  
Defend (Main characters only): 2d6 \+ Body vs. 8  
If hit, take 1d6 damage.  
Zero HP \= knocked out, fainted, stars for eyes, pick it back up next scene.  
Players: 5 HP, Goons and minions: 1-3, no defense rolls.  
Vehicles (mecha, spaceships, special sidekicks): 10 HP  
Special Abilities: 1 use per scene. Boosts a stat roll or triggers a cool effect.  
Gear: \+3 to a roll or damage (usually once per scenario).  
Optional: After a session, tweak 1 stat or evolve your Special to match the story.

SCENE ONE: THE WELCOMING COMMITTEE  
You spot movement near the endcap stacked with organic oats.

SCENE TWO: FRESH FRUIT FOR ROTTING VEGGIES  
The produce here is... off. The bananas are whispering apologies. The avocados have names and expiry dates written on their skins. A spectral employee offers a sample of ghostly kale chips ("vegan, paleo, and pre-digested").

SCENE THREE: AT THE FREEZERS OF MADNESS  
The frozen aisle runs coldest where the endcaps lie empty. Follow the dry ice fog and ignore the screaming mochi. The floor grows slick. The fog thickens. Suddenly, a Sampler Drone—half freezer, half evangelist—emerges, offering gyoza on toothpicks... but its voice is stuck in a loop:  
  **“Try the dumplings… TRY the dumplings… TRY—”**  
Its heating coil glows red.

SCENE FOUR: RITUALS FOR RESTOCKING  
The endcaps consist of a pyramid of gluten-free fear bricks and a softly humming pyramid of Grocer Gene’s Chicken Marsala That Knows Your Secrets. You see the Cookie Butter at the far end of the aisle—surrounded by dancing Fear Greeters performing the Restocking Ritual.

SCENE FIVE: DRY CEREAL IS THE TRUE HORROR  
The group plunges into the Dairy/Nondairy Convergence Zone. It’s cold. Too cold. The signage contradicts itself.  
  **“Oat Milk: Aisle 4”**  
  **“Aisle 4 does not exist.”**  
  **“All Oats Have Been Accounted For.”**  
Fluorescent lights flicker overhead. A spectral Milkmonger hovers by the cases, swirling a vat of liquid memory and judgement. Oat milk cartons float around him like orbiting moons—each labeled with emotionally specific slogans:  
  **“Regret-Free.”**  
  **“For That One Time You Tried Yoga.”**  
  **“Best Served During Apologies.”**

SCENE SIX: THE MOST FEARFUL OF FLIERS  
The group, inspired by a sudden burst shelving wisdom, and sees a barely visible alcove marked with a plaque:  
  **“Printed Propaganda Archives – Staff Only.”**  
There, in a corner pulsing faintly with nostalgia and printer toner, lies a rotting wire rack stacked with ancient, brittle Fearful Flier back issues.  
They whisper deal terms and discontinued seasonal favorites.  
One of them tries to bite.

SCENE SEVEN: I DON’T WANT TO SPEAK TO THE MANAGER  
A spectral Manager Emeritus rises from the filing cabinet beneath.  
  **“WHO DARES UN-SHELF WHAT WAS RETIRED?”**  
The ghost flickers in and out of OSHA compliance, clipboard in hand, discounts etched in ectoplasm. The room chills. All flyers begin fluttering. One whispers:  
  **“Only one can claim the Final Coupon.”**
